    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-21T16:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-21T16:30:00-05:00" n="301"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/3817a: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-21T17:30:00-04:00"
                            >May 21, 1943—5:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–1766. The U.S. Immigration Service is planning to provide a train at shipside
                    on the West Coast for the Polish refugees to transport <pb facs="0316" n="306"
                        xml:id="pg_306"/> them through to Mexico City and incidentally to provide
                    medical care for them en route. The Immigration Service has suggested the
                    desirability of your arranging with the Mexican Immigration Service for their
                    reception at the border in order to facilitate the arrival of the train in
                    Mexico City without delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
